HEADWORD: Bilifuscin
<hw>Bil`i*fus"cin</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>bilis</ets> bile + <ets>fuscus</ets> dark.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>A brownish green pigment found in human
gallstones and in old bile. It is a derivative of bilirubin.</def>⟦br⟧
